REMARK. — The specimens from south 
<collectingCountry id="12ED763D2E7EFFC8FB308C6BFAB2F867" box="[1187,1312,1897,1921]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="48" pageNumber="73">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
are very rufous on the undertail, with a reddish hue extending on the vent. A hybrid zone/introgression with 
<emphasis id="588EEABF2E7EFFC8FB868C9DFB1AF851" box="[1045,1160,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="73">T. rufiventer</emphasis>
should be considered. Further field and genetic research on this species and the closely relatives are greatly needed (cfr. 
<bibRefCitation id="0E6B4B5C2E7EFFC8FC788CD1FB00F80C" author="FABRE P. H. &amp; IRESTEDT M. &amp; FJELDSA J. &amp; BRISTOL R. &amp; GROOMBRIDGE J. J. &amp; IRHAM M. &amp; JONSSON K. A." box="[1003,1170,2003,2027]" pageId="48" pageNumber="73" pagination="1900 - 1918" refId="ref65873" refString="FABRE P. H., IRESTEDT M., FJELDSA J., BRISTOL R., GROOMBRIDGE J. J., IRHAM M., &amp; JONSSON K. A. (2012). - Dynamic colonization exchanges between continents and islands drive diversification in paradise-flycatchers (Terpsiphone, Monarchidae). Journal of Biogeography 39: 1900 - 1918." type="journal article" year="2012">
Fabre 
<emphasis id="588EEABF2E7EFFC8FBB48CD6FBC4F80C" box="[1063,1110,2003,2027]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
